Subject: RE: [VB] Wobbly belt?

Did the pulley checks, even blamed my new motor for excessive endplay,
but no wiggles at either end. The wobble is only on the side of the belt
closest to carb, and is about 1/4" in movement. Even disappears above
1700rpm, but slight and noticible at idle. Pulleys are lined up and
tight. Perhaps gen bearing had become eccentric somehow? No noises
besides a Volkswagen engine.
I am adjusting valves one more time since we now have 150 miles (just
did oil change 3)...Storage immenent for PA winter...
Found little particles of nasties in my oil, some more assembly lube at
drain pan bottom, think she's at all oil now! W0000!
Al


